3.	Explain the McCulloch–Pitts model of neuron.
Ans=McCulloch-Pitts Model of neuron is divide into two part one is summation and second is activation function . summation collects all input and add it with the weights and bais.  

4.	Explain the ADALINE network model.
Ans=ADALINE network model stands for the adaptive linear neuron .It uses the Delta rule which minimise the mean squared error 

5.	What is the constraint of a simple perceptron? Why it may fail with a real-world data set?
Ans=simple perceptron required a linear input and give bipolar input (0,1).
If we provide the non-linear function provide  then it is difficult for classification

6.	What is linearly inseparable problem? What is the role of the hidden layer?
Ans = when the data is not categorised by the linear boundary then that’s problem is linearly inseparable problem . The hidden layer are used to simplify the complexity of the input it combines the input as per the number of the neuron and give one output .we can select the number of hidden layer as per the problem generally we use two hidden layer. But not select many hidden layer because it results overfitting 

7.	Explain XOR problem in case of a simple perceptron.
       Ans=XOR or Exclusive OR gives boolen type of output if inputs of perceptron are different then it     give output as true otherwise False 

