12.	What are the advantages and disadvantages of neural networks?
Advantages=
-it is not required to train the model again and again
-it work with the linear as well as non-linear function also
-neural network are flexible 
Disadvantages
-it have black box nature 
-it requires much more data to train
-it is also depend on the hardware also
13.	Write short notes on any two of the following:
1.	Biological neuron
Ans= Biological neuron contain dendrite, Cell ,Axon. Its have one network called neural network . all network work on impulse which transfer the message from one neuron to another and finally give output  
2.	ReLU function
=it stands for Rectified Linear Activation function , it is one type of activation function and very efficient
3.	Single-layer feed forward ANN
=feed forward artificial neural network not work in loop having one flow of data from input layer to output via hidden layer to decrease the complexity of the problem to give correct prediction
4.	Gradient descent
=gradient descent is the activation function used to train neural network 
5.	Recurrent networks
=In the recurrent neural network the prediction is depend on with  previous one 

